The paper discusses a security aspect of machine learning in wireless communications, specifically in the context of spectrum sensing and data transmission. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Given the focus on adversarial machine learning and the use of deep neural network models, cs.CR and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The use of wireless communications and spectrum sensing also suggests cs.NI as a possible category. cs.SY and cs.AI are less likely but still possible categories given the focus on control and decision-making in the context of machine learning.
